<P>Secondly, from the beginning of all things. <NOTE PLACE="inter">N&eacute;zetata&ucirc;we, waske nouj&agrave;iitch wame aiakquiiks,</NOTE> that have a dependant being. For <NOTE PLACE="inter">teous uttahh&ecirc;nau rambatsen pummaiawunk. Wutche</NOTE> the things which had a beginning could not be cause <NOTE PLACE="inter">aiak quiiks teous noujaiiggishhansh, matta hom w&acirc;je</NOTE> of their own being, for that wh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">ch is not <NOTE PLACE="inter">pummaiaw&uacute;nganoo, wutche ne matta pummaynook</NOTE> cannot act, nor could any thing <NOTE PLACE="inter">matta hom r&eacute;manoo chaugun, matta hom chaugun</NOTE> be before it was therefore it must <NOTE PLACE="inter">pumm&acirc;io, askam pumm&acirc;y n&oacute;shan, newutche paughke</NOTE> have its beginning from <NOTE PLACE="inter">[m&ocirc;uchh]out&agrave;hh&egrave;amo noujaiewunk wutche chaugun</NOTE> some other cause which is without beginning <NOTE PLACE="inter">now&eacute;ta perrewawhjaioohittit teou matta outchinoh,</NOTE> and therefore the first <NOTE PLACE="inter">[mehchu noujaiewunk] quah n&egrave;-wutche negonne</NOTE> being and efficient cause of all <NOTE PLACE="inter">pummayawunk quah kezh&uacute;wan waje wutche wame</NOTE> other being. <NOTE PLACE="inter">unkatagganakpum mayaw&uacute;ngansh.</NOTE></P>
