<DIV1 TYPE="question">
<HEAD>How can you know that there is a God, seeing <NOTE PLACE="inter"><HI>Ob:</HI> Ten h&ocirc;n kuttaw&aacute;uhtaun ne atta Mando maetax</NOTE> you never saw him, nor can see him? <NOTE PLACE="inter">keken&acirc;uwah, matta h&ocirc;m nauwo?</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>I know I have a reasonable <NOTE PLACE="inter"><HI>An.</HI> Nouw&aacute;uht&acirc;un no wadj&acirc;naman penaun&acirc;uwe</NOTE> soul, though I never saw it, nor can <NOTE PLACE="inter">mittachonkq, mukko matta ne nauwah matta h&ocirc;m</NOTE> see it. The soul were not a spirituall <NOTE PLACE="inter">nauwo. Mittachonkq matta hom rasha wr&aacute;ndowe</NOTE> substance if it could be seen with bodily eyes, <NOTE PLACE="inter">pumm&acirc;yawunk h&ocirc;m na&uuml; wit spe hogg&acirc;uwe skesuks,</NOTE> and so no soul In like manner were not a Spirit <NOTE PLACE="inter">qu&aacute;h ri&ograve; matta o&uacute;tachonq. Rio God matta rashau|wandoo,</NOTE> if he could be seen with bodily eyes and so <NOTE PLACE="inter">om na&ucirc; wit spe hogg&acirc;uwe skesuks; quah rio</NOTE> no God. <NOTE PLACE="inter">matta Mando.</NOTE></P>
