<PB N="30" REF="21">
lesse how to plant and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">overn Com|mon-weales <NOTE PLACE="inter">ten r&eacute;okkechan, quah soudamot&acirc;u&ocirc;an korta|so&ocirc;domo&uacute;ngansh;</NOTE> or to become learned <NOTE PLACE="inter">ux koodamanchan wnskwhagana|kre,</NOTE> or sayl over the Seas, &amp;c. For <NOTE PLACE="inter">ux sebogh&oacute;mman akk&oacute;mmuk kathans, &amp;c. Wut|che</NOTE> these things exceed their <NOTE PLACE="inter">yous aiakquiiks [remuks] &aacute;rrookaw&aacute;uw&aacute;unk ne|jek</NOTE> capacities in like manner man seeing <NOTE PLACE="inter">wa&uacute;htamma w&uacute;nganoo rio ren nauwun ewo</NOTE> himselfe to be made of a more noble nature <NOTE PLACE="inter">hoggakezhean wutche arwen&uacute;guot arrumb&acirc;uwunk</NOTE> then beasts, and that not of <NOTE PLACE="inter">a&ucirc;sinre oppishimmok, quah youh matta wutche</NOTE> him selfe, must <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">eeds inferre that he <NOTE PLACE="inter">nagum hogga, pauhke moushe pakadoowun ne h&ocirc;|wan</NOTE> who made him superiour to beasts, he <NOTE PLACE="inter">kezhuwus uw&acirc;io arr&ocirc;okawah oppishim, ewo</NOTE> no lesse above man, th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">n man is above <NOTE PLACE="inter">ausinre arr&ocirc;okawah ren&ocirc;ok arra ren arr&ocirc;okawant</NOTE> beasts; and therefore that the full knowledge <NOTE PLACE="inter">oppishshim; quah n&egrave;gouche ne tab&acirc;io wauhtawunk</NOTE> of his nature <NOTE PLACE="inter">wutche uwio arr&aacute;ndoit [&aacute;rrum&agrave;uwunk] &acirc;usin</NOTE> exceeds mans capacity. <NOTE PLACE="inter">err&ocirc;okawah renna kitchshant&agrave;mmoowunk.</NOTE></P>
