<DIV1 TYPE="question">
<PB N="31" REF="22">
<HEAD>How do you prove that there is but one true <NOTE PLACE="inter"><HI>Q.</HI> To gouje kor&aacute;men n<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters"> webe p&acirc;suk wah werremat</NOTE> God? <NOTE PLACE="inter">Iehovah?</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Because the reason why singular <NOTE PLACE="inter"><HI>An.</HI> Wutche wai&acirc;iewunk toh&oacute;dje nans&acirc;iewok</NOTE> things of the same kind are multi|plyed <NOTE PLACE="inter">aiakquiiks w&uacute;tche ans&eacute;jekmuche nenar kokk&ocirc;odish|ah<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">awk</NOTE> is not to be sound in the nature <NOTE PLACE="inter">matta misskommauwa&ucirc;o&acirc;n r&acirc;me &agrave;rumb&acirc;u|wunk</NOTE> of for the reason <NOTE PLACE="inter">ar&aacute;ndoit] wutche God; wuche waj&acirc;iewunk</NOTE> why such like things are multiplyed is <NOTE PLACE="inter">tohodje ars&ocirc;auk aiakquiiks kokk&ocirc;odishh&eacute;auk atta</NOTE> from the fruitfulnesse of their causes: <NOTE PLACE="inter">wutche hokkiss&egrave;gowunk wutche wajaiwunganooas:</NOTE> but hath no cause of <NOTE PLACE="inter">webe God matta ou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">a~he waj&acirc;iewunk wutche</NOTE> his being, but is of himself <NOTE PLACE="inter">uw&acirc;io pumma&icirc;ewunk, webe wutche nagum hogga</NOTE> therefore he is one. <NOTE PLACE="inter">neg&ocirc;uche papasaqun.</NOTE></P>
<P N="2">2. Because singular things of <NOTE PLACE="inter">Newutche nans&acirc;ioaks ai&agrave;kquiiks wutche</NOTE> the same kind when they are multiplyed, are <NOTE PLACE="inter">nenar &acirc;rak nants&eacute;jek kokkoodrishshahettit, &agrave;chabis|soh&egrave;awawk</NOTE> differenced among them selves by <NOTE PLACE="inter">yar&acirc;u we n&agrave;gam&aacute;uwo hogg&acirc;uwo we&ecirc;che</NOTE> their singular properties; but there <NOTE PLACE="inter">nejek nanseas artumbauhittaw &uacute;ngansh webe muche</NOTE> cannot be found another God differenced <NOTE PLACE="inter">hom matta sk&ocirc;wah, unkatak Mando achabizh&eacute;an</NOTE> from this by any such like propertyes. <NOTE PLACE="inter">wutche y&ocirc;uh spe chawgunsh arr&acirc;ious &agrave;chabissew&ucirc;n|gansh [arramb&acirc;muks.</NOTE></P>
<P N="3"><PB N="32" REF="22">
3. Because its proper to God <NOTE PLACE="inter">N&egrave;wutche webe mohtantammim re Jehovah</NOTE> to do whatsoever he willeth; if there were many Gods they <NOTE PLACE="inter">u<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">&egrave;ein hanharroytaks, hom sharehit Mandoak hom</NOTE> might will contrary things, and one might be hindred by <NOTE PLACE="inter">&oacute;pperrew&oacute;rrantammock, quah nejek hom wowotam|hittawawk</NOTE> another, so that he could not do what he <NOTE PLACE="inter">r&ecirc;an chawgun rio matta hom re kaddau|we<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">&egrave;atteou</NOTE> would, which can not stand with the Omni|potency <NOTE PLACE="inter">hom matta toukranah weeche wame keiz|tauwunganuk</NOTE> and nature of God. <NOTE PLACE="inter">quah arrandoit Jehovah.</NOTE></P>
</DIV1>
